UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc2='Oh it\'s just so horrible, $G sir:miss;. The house Barov was once full of life... full of splendor. The manor was the Barov\'s primary residence amidst their far reaching empire.$B$BLucien and I noticed that as the days progressed, the Barovs became depressed. Despondent. Paranoia and rage often overcame the master and misses. At night, we could hear the Barovs arguing in their chambers. From what we understood, their greed had \'broken the dam,\' so to speak.',Text1_0_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4043;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc2='Restraints? There are things in this world far more restraining than bars and shackles, young $G master:mistress;. The undead surrounded us, constantly tormenting us with horrifying acts of depravity.$B$BFinally, he came. He introduced himself as Doctor Theolen Krastinov. We came to know him as \'The Butcher.\'',Text0_1_loc2='Restraints? There are things in this world far more restraining than bars and shackles, young $G master:mistress;. The undead surrounded us, constantly tormenting us with horrifying acts of depravity.$B$BFinally, he came. He introduced himself as Doctor Theolen Krastinov. We came to know him as \'The Butcher.\'',Text1_0_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4047;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc2='We finally understood what the screams were from. The Butcher exposed us to pain that we did not know existed. He used us in countless experiments, attempting to devise a plague.$B$BThe days turned to weeks. We would have died on the first day had it not been for that cruel bastard keeping us alive through magical means.',Text1_0_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc2='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4048;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc2='We don\'t have a bank here in Brill, you\'ll have to go to the Undercity for that.  At the back of the Ruins of Lordaeron to the south are elevators that will take you down into the Undercity.  Once there ask one of the Undercity Guardians for more precise directions.',Text0_1_loc2='We don\'t have a bank here in Brill, you\'ll have to go to the Undercity for that.  At the back of the Ruins of Lordaeron to the south are elevators that will take you down into the Undercity.  Once there ask one of the Undercity Guardians for more precise directions.' WHERE entry=4074;
